Treznor is the man who looks after the wood tree farming patch in Varrock. As Treznor is part of the Group of Advanced Gardeners, players can use him as one of the five gardeners they must speak to during the Fairy Tale I - Growing Pains quest.

Shop[edit | edit source]

Treznor also sells basic farming tools, which can be accessed by talking to him and asking Can you sell me something? It is not an actual shop and it has no set stock; each item has to be bought individually through the dialogue.

(update)

Gardeners at farming patches now sell plant pots.

Treznor, the farmer at Varrock's tree patch no longer wanders so far from the patch.

Trivia[edit | edit source]

  • His name is a reference to Trent Reznor, the frontman of Nine Inch Nails.[1]
  • In the 11th issue of the Postbag from the Hedge, his moniker is revealed to be "Treznor the Grubby".

References[edit | edit source]

  1. ^ Jagex. Mod Ash's Twitter account. 07 August 2019. (Archived from the original on 30 May 2020.) Mod Ash: "The dev is no longer here to ask, but I believe he confirmed that it is indeed such a reference when he still worked here."
